\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Trajectory dynamics and regime occupancy.} (\textbf  {A})~Variance minimization landscape $F(\varphi , R)/k_BT = \sigma ^{2}(\varphi , R)$. The black curve traces the minimum-variance trajectory from $R = 0.3$ (Turbulent) to $R = 0.95$ (Coherent). (\textbf  {B})~Kuramoto $R(t)$ trajectory over 120~s for healthy (green, $R \approx 0.95$) and depressed (red, $R \approx 0.30$) subjects. Shaded bands mark Coherent ($R > 0.8$) and Turbulent ($R < 0.3$) regimes. (\textbf  {C})~Poincar\'e section: $R_{n+1}$ versus $R_n$ for successive time windows. Healthy trajectories cluster tightly near $(0.95, 0.95)$ with no exact returns; depressed trajectories show broader scatter near $(0.3, 0.3)$. (\textbf  {D})~Regime occupancy fractions for four conditions. Healthy: predominantly Coherent/Cascade. Depressed: predominantly Turbulent. N3~Sleep and REM show intermediate and turbulent profiles respectively.}}{8}{figure.caption.6}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:dynamics}{{1}{8}{\textbf {Trajectory dynamics and regime occupancy.} (\textbf {A})~Variance minimization landscape $F(\varphi , R)/k_BT = \sigma ^{2}(\varphi , R)$. The black curve traces the minimum-variance trajectory from $R = 0.3$ (Turbulent) to $R = 0.95$ (Coherent). (\textbf {B})~Kuramoto $R(t)$ trajectory over 120~s for healthy (green, $R \approx 0.95$) and depressed (red, $R \approx 0.30$) subjects. Shaded bands mark Coherent ($R > 0.8$) and Turbulent ($R < 0.3$) regimes. (\textbf {C})~Poincar\'e section: $R_{n+1}$ versus $R_n$ for successive time windows. Healthy trajectories cluster tightly near $(0.95, 0.95)$ with no exact returns; depressed trajectories show broader scatter near $(0.3, 0.3)$. (\textbf {D})~Regime occupancy fractions for four conditions. Healthy: predominantly Coherent/Cascade. Depressed: predominantly Turbulent. N3~Sleep and REM show intermediate and turbulent profiles respectively}{figure.caption.6}{}}
