\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Pharmacological scale validation.} (\textbf  {A})~Drug profiles in S-entropy space ($S_k$, $S_t$, $S_e$), colored by drug class: SSRI (green), SNRI (blue), TCA (red), Atypical (orange). (\textbf  {B})~Binding affinity profiles across receptor targets for six antidepressants. Dashed line marks $K_i = 100$~nM threshold separating high- from low-affinity interactions. (\textbf  {C})~Clinical response rates by drug. Gray band indicates convergence zone ($\sim \!60 \pm 3\%$). Markers above bars denote aperture type: circle (monopole), square (dipole), diamond (quadrupole). (\textbf  {D})~Selectivity ratio versus categorical distance $d_{\mathrm  {cat}}$, colored by clinical response rate. The absence of strong correlation supports cross-modal equivalence.}}{12}{figure.caption.10}\protected@file@percent }
